title: For Sale:  “Classic” 1911 Style:  Star 45 ACP Model PD
postcontent:
Compact model is great for concealed carry.
One of the most accurate compact 45 autos I’ve had.
 
Inspired by the famous 1911 Design: This is a beauty of a gun and “Classic” all the way: Solidly built with Star’s weapons grade steel slide, parts and barrel. Forged steel parts as it precedes the age of MIM. This gun represents the classic style of handguns with forged steel manufacturing, instead of stamped steel, alloy frames, plastic and polymer so common today. 
Mid-size gun is compact and great for concealed carry as it's extremely flat.  Similar to the classic 1911 Colt Commander.
Performance and Handling: Like so many other Star pistols, it is a very stable, tame shooter in your hand. Recoil is light and still very controllable even with hot loads. Love the accuracy and reliability shooting all kinds of ammo, JHP, etc. 
Colt 1911 Commonalities:   The many similarities to the 1911 ACP make this pistol a favorite. First, the look and feel are squarely 1911. That very classic and natural pick up.
Action & Trigger: single-action with locked breech. Single action trigger break is excellent – very clean! Serrated finger pad for a sure grip.
 PREMIUM FEATURES:
Safeties: Thumb safety on left side like the Colt 1911. You can carry cocked and locked. Gun also has a Magazine Disconnect for additional safety.
Sights: notched rear blade and serrated front ramp. Easy to pick up at speed. The sight picture is easy to obtain in both slow and rapid-fire drills. The rear sight is drift adjustable for windage and elevation!
Full-length guide rod with captive recoil spring.
Removable barrel bushing.
  
As a testament to their quality, Star BM is still used by police, security and military agencies in Spain. The PD stands for Police Department as these were designed for the police in Spain.  It reflects the reliability, durability and the quality of Spanish pistols and to the skill and workmanship of the workers of Star Firearms Bonifacio.
Conclusion:  The easy handling and resemblances to the classic Colt 1911 make this pistol a favorite among collectors, recreational shooters, or carry owners.
 
 
OTHER INFORMATION:
History & Origins: After the First World War started, Star designers fell in love with the Colt 1911 and focused on cloning it (instead of other European designs). After the war, many US soldiers liked the similar to their 1911 and brought back Star pistols to the US. Many others bought them when offered commercially, don’t want to part with them and still carry them.* This item is for sale.  It is not necessary to ask if it is still available.  If you are reading the ad, it is available.(No trades.  No silly low offers - those messages will not be returned.)
